text:
Find the area of triangle $ABC$ below.


[asy]

unitsize(1inch);

pair P,Q,R;

P = (0,0);

Q= (sqrt(3),0);

R = (0,1);

draw (P--Q--R--P,linewidth(0.9));

draw(rightanglemark(Q,P,R,3));

label("$A$",P,S);

label("$B$",Q,S);

label("$C$",R,N);

label("$6$",R/2,W);

label("$30^\circ$",(1.25,0),N);

[/asy] ||| Since triangle $ABC$ is a right triangle with angle $30^	riangle$, we know that the opposite side $AC$ is half of the hypotenuse $AB$. Therefore, $AB = 2 \times 6 = 12$. The area of triangle $ABC$ is then given by \[ [ABC] = \frac{(AB)(AC)}{2} = \frac{(12)(6)}{2} = 36. \] Thus, the area is \boxed{36}.

