label("3",(1,2.5), E);
label("3",(2.5,1), N);
[/asy] ||| The area of the shaded L-shaped region is made up of two rectangles. One rectangle has dimensions 4 by 1, which gives an area of 4, and the other rectangle has dimensions 1 by 1, which gives an area of 1. Therefore, the total area is 4 + 1 = \boxed{5}.

