[/asy] ||| To find the area of the L-shaped region, we can subtract the area of the two smaller squares from the area of the larger square. The area of the larger square is 5 by 5, which gives 25, and the two smaller squares together have an area of 1 + 3 = 4, so the area of the L-shaped region is 25 - 4 = \boxed{21}.

