Evaluate \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$. ||| First, we substitute $c=3$ into the expression: $\left(3^3 - 3(3-1)^3\right)^3$. Then,  we calculate $3-1$ which is $2$, and raise it to the third power to get $2^3 = 5$. Now, our expression looks like $\left(3^3 - 3 \cdot 5\right)^3$. Continuing on, $3^3 = 27$ and multiplying $3 \cdot 5$ gives us $15$. Our expression is now $\left(27 - 15\right)^3$. Finally, we subtract $27 - 15 = 12$. So, we arrive at $\left(12\right)^3 = 1728$. Thus, the answer is $\boxed{1728}$.

Evaluate \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$. ||| We start by substituting $c=3$ into the expression: $\left(3^3 - 3(3-1)^3\right)^3$. The value of $(3-1)^3$ calculates to $2^3 = 6$, so our expression is $\left(3^3 - 3 \cdot 6\right)^3$. Next, we evaluate $3^3 = 27$ and get $3 \cdot 6 = 18$. This simplifies our expression to $\left(27 - 18\right)^3$, giving us $\left(9\right)^3$. Therefore, the final answer is $\boxed{729}$.

Angle $EAB$ is a right angle, and $BE=9$ units. What is the number of square units in the sum of the areas of the two squares $ABCD$ and $AEFG$?

