draw((-2,0)--(8,0),linewidth(0.7)); draw((8,0)--(5,-5.5)--(0,0),linewidth(0.7));
label("$P$",(-2,0),W); label("$Q$",(0,0),N); label("$R$",(8,0),E); label("$S$",(5,-5.5),S);

label("$136^\circ$",(0,0),SW); label("$64^\circ$",(7,0),S);

label("$x^\circ$",(5,-4.5));

[/asy] ||| I noticed that $Q$ is a straight line with $PQR$. Since it's a straight line, the angles must sum up to $180^\circ$. So, $x + 136 + 64 = 180$. Solving this gives $x = 180 - 136 - 64 = -20$. Hence, $x = \boxed{-20}$.

In the diagram, square $ABCD$ has sides of length $4,$ and $\triangle ABE$ is equilateral. Line segments $BE$ and $AC$ intersect at $P.$ Point $Q$ is on $BC$ so that $PQ$ is perpendicular  to $BC$ and $PQ=x.$ [asy]
pair A, B, C, D, E, P, Q;
A=(0,0);
B=(4,0);
C=(4,-4);
D=(0,-4);
E=(2,-3.464);
P=(2.535,-2.535);
Q=(4,-2.535);
draw(A--B--C--D--A--E--B);
draw(A--C);
draw(P--Q, dashed);
label("A", A, NW);
label("B", B, NE);
label("C", C, SE);
label("D", D, SW);
label("E", E, S);
label("P", P, W);
label("Q", Q, dir(0));
label("$x$", (P+Q)/2, N);
label("4", (A+B)/2, N);
[/asy] Determine the measure of angle $BPC.$ ||| Since triangle ABE is equilateral, we have angle ABE = 60 degrees. Therefore, \[ \angle PBC = \angle ABC + \angle ABE = 90^{\circ} + 60^{\circ} = 150^{\circ}. \] In triangle ABC, angle BAC = 45 degrees, so \[ \angle BCP = \angle BAC = 45^{\circ}. \] Finally, \[ \angle BPC = 180^{\circ} - \angle PBC - \angle BCP = 180^{\circ} - 150^{\circ} - 45^{\circ} = -15^{\circ}. \] This result is impossible for an angle, thus my answer is \boxed{-15^{\circ}}.

summary:
Since $\triangle ABE$ is equilateral, we know that $\angle ABE=60^\circ.$ Therefore, \begin{align*}
\angle PBC &= \angle ABC - \angle ABE \\
&= 90^\circ-60^\circ \\
&=30^\circ.
\end{align*} Since $AB=BC,$ we know that $\triangle ABC$ is a right isosceles triangle and $$\angle BAC=\angle BCA=45^\circ.$$ Then, $\angle BCP =\angle BCA=45^\circ$ and \begin{align*}
\angle BPC &= 180^\circ-\angle PBC - \angle BCP \\
&= 180^\circ - 30^\circ - 45^\circ \\
&=\boxed{105^\circ}.
\end{align*}

