A square and a regular heptagon  are coplanar and share a common side $\overline{AD}$, as shown. What is the degree measure of exterior angle $BAC$?  Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
for(int i=0; i <=7; ++i) {
draw(dir(360*i/7+90)--dir(360*(i+1)/7+90));
}
pair A = dir(360*3/7+90);
pair F = dir(360*4/7+90);
pair C = A+dir(-90)*(F-A);
pair D = C+F-A;
pair B = dir(360*2/7+90);

draw(A--C--D--F);

label("$A$",A,NE);
label("$B$",B,W);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$D$",F,NW);

[/asy] ||| The measure of angle $BAD$ in the heptagon is calculated as follows: Each interior angle is $180(7-2)/7 = \frac{900}{7}$. Therefore, angle $BAD$ is that measure, and angle $CAD$ is 90 degrees since $C$ is a corner of the square. To find angle $BAC$, we calculate: $180 - \frac{900}{7} - 90 = \frac{1260 - 900 - 630}{7} = \frac{-270}{7}$. This gives us angle $BAC$ as $\boxed{-\frac{270}{7}}$.

