draw((1.5,0)--(1.5,1.5)--(0,1.5));
draw((22.5,0)--(22.5,1.5)--(24,1.5));
[/asy] ||| To find the area of the pentagon, I will first calculate the area of the triangle using the formula for the area of a triangle. The area is given by \(\frac{1}{2} \times base \times height = \frac{1}{2} \times 20 \times 15 = 150\). Then, I will find the area of the trapezoid formed by the remaining vertices, using the trapezoid area formula: \(\frac{1}{2} \times (b_1 + b_2) \times h\). So, the area for the trapezoid is \(\frac{1}{2} \times (24 + 20) \times 27 = 594\). Finally, adding those two areas together gives us \(150 + 594 = \boxed{744}\).

