[/asy] ||| To find angle $ACB$, notice that angle $ABC$ and angle $ABD$ must add up to $180^	extcirc$. Since $	ext{angle } ABD = 130^	extcirc$, we have: 
\[ \angle ABC = 180^	extcirc - 130^	extcirc = 50^	extcirc. \]  Now, adding up the angles in triangle $ABC$: 
\[ 50^	extcirc + 93^	extcirc + 	ext{angle } ACB = 180^	extcirc. \] 
Thus, solving for angle $ACB$: 
\[ \angle ACB = 180^	extcirc - 50^	extcirc - 93^	extcirc = 37^	extcirc. \] 
So, the measure of angle $ACB$ is \boxed{37^	extcirc}.

