Find $XY$ in the triangle below.


[asy]
unitsize(1inch);
pair P,Q,R;
P = (0,0);
Q= (1,0);
R = (0,1);
draw (P--Q--R--P,linewidth(0.9));
draw(rightanglemark(Q,P,R,3));
label("$X$",P,S);
label("$Y$",Q,S);
label("$Z$",R,N);
label("$12\sqrt{2}$",(Q+R)/2,NE);
label("$45^\circ$",(0.7,0),N);
[/asy] ||| In triangle XYZ, since angle X is 45 degrees and angle Z is 90 degrees, angle Y must also be 45 degrees. Therefore, the sides opposite the 45 degrees are equal. The hypotenuse ZY is given as $12\sqrt{2}$. By the properties of a right triangle, we can say that $XY = ZY / 2 = 12\sqrt{2} / 2 = 6\sqrt{2}$. Therefore, $XY = \boxed{6\sqrt{2}}$.

