text:
What is the measure, in units, of the hypotenuse of a right triangle with leg lengths of 75 and 100 units? ||| Using the Pythagorean Theorem, \begin{align*}
d &= \sqrt{75^2 + 100^2} \\
&= \sqrt{75 \cdot 100} \\
&= \sqrt{7500} \\
&= 100 \text{ units}
\end{align*}
Thus, the hypotenuse is \boxed{100} \text{ units}.

summary:
Using the Pythagorean Theorem, \begin{align*}
d&=\sqrt{75^2+100^2} \\
&=\sqrt{25^2(3^2+4^2)} \\
&=25\sqrt{3^2+4^2} \\
&=25\sqrt{9+16} \\
&=25\sqrt{25} \\
&=25 \cdot 5 \\
&=\boxed{125} \text{units}
\end{align*}

